article.headline: Cornell 75, Bucknell 64
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow; Cornell 75, Bucknell 64. ITHACA, N.Y. -- Louis Dale had 20 points, 10 rebounds and five assists as Cornell scored 52 second-half points and beat Bucknell 75-64 on Tuesday night. Ryan Wittman added 17 points, freshman Chris Wroblewski had a career-high 13, and Jeff Foote had 12 points, nine rebounds and five blocks for the Big Red (9-6), who won their fourth in a row. Bryan Cohen had 20 points and G.W. Boon had 15 to lead the Bison (3-11), who lost to Cornell for the first time in six meetings. After shooting just 28 percent in the first half, Cornell connected on 15-of-23 shots after halftime. The Big Red also limited Bucknell to 38 percent shooting for the game and outrebounded the Bison 40-31.
